Desc: Nintendo Switch is designed to fit your life, transforming from home console to portable system in a snap.
Joy-Cons are the primary game controllers for the Nintendo Switch video game console. They consist of two individual units, each containing an analog stick and an array of buttons.

The Pro Controller features two analog control sticks, the traditional ABXY configuration, an eight-way directional Control Pad, and four shoulder buttons. There are also Home, Plus, Minus, and Capture buttons on the controller.
Super Mario Odyssey is a 2017 action-adventure platform game developed and published by Nintendo for the Nintendo Switch video game console.

Mario Kart 8 is a kart racing game developed and published by Nintendo, and first released for the Wii U in 2014. It retains Mario Kart series game mechanics, where players control Mario franchise characters in kart racing, collecting a variety of items to hinder opponents or gain advantages in the race.
PlayStation®5: The PS5™ console unleashes new gaming possibilities that you never anticipated.
The DualSense Wireless Controller is the controller for PS5 including several next-generation features like haptic feedback and dynamic adaptive triggers.
Elden Ring is an action role-playing game developed by FromSoftware and published by Bandai Namco Entertainment.
Marvels Spider-Man: Miles Morales is a 2020 action-adventure game developed by Insomniac Games and published by Sony Interactive Entertainment.
Deathloop is a 2021 first-person shooter video game developed by Arkane Studios and published by Bethesda Softworks.

Halo Infinite is a 2021 first-person shooter game developed by 343 Industries and published by Xbox Game Studios.
Assassins Creed Valhalla is a 2020 action role-playing video game developed by Ubisoft Montreal and published by Ubisoft.
